T1  - When is an aggregate of a time series efficiently forecast by its past?
AU  - Kohn, Robert
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 18
IS  - 3
SP  - 337
EP  - 349
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/04/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(82)90087-2
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407682900872
AB  - The paper gives necessary and sufficient conditions for a linear combination of the elements of a vector time series to be efficiently forecast by its own past values, where by past we mean both the infinite and also the finite past. We observe that the problem is equivalent to testing a single element of a vector for exogeneity, this observation also suggesting a method for empirically testing the derived conditions.
ER  - 
